From: John Kleinschmidt <jkleinsc@electronjs.org>
Date: Fri, 24 Jul 2026 13:02:49 -0400
Subject: fix: guard WebstorePrivateApi factory against null delegate

The WebstorePrivate API was moved to //extensions (CL 7874276), and its
KeyedService factory is now built unconditionally from the shared
EnsureApiBrowserContextKeyedServiceFactoriesBuilt(). The factory's
dependencies are obtained from a WebstorePrivateAPIDelegate provided by the
embedder via ExtensionsAPIClient. Electron does not support the
webstorePrivate API and does not provide a delegate, so building the factory
dereferenced a null delegate and crashed at startup.

Skip building the factory when no delegate is available.

diff --git a/extensions/browser/api/webstore_private/webstore_private_api.cc b/extensions/browser/api/webstore_private/webstore_private_api.cc
index 7702598c7136bb482abaca5d58a84788e2d0469b..fe048d37126c5465a8d8aa8bb2539a86a013bde4 100644
--- a/extensions/browser/api/webstore_private/webstore_private_api.cc
+++ b/extensions/browser/api/webstore_private/webstore_private_api.cc
@@ -478,6 +478,12 @@ WebstorePrivateApi::PopApprovalForTesting(  // IN-TEST
 
 // static
 void WebstorePrivateApi::EnsureAssociatedFactoryBuilt() {
+  // The factory's dependencies are obtained from the embedder-provided
+  // WebstorePrivateAPIDelegate. Embedders that do not support the
+  // webstorePrivate API (e.g. Electron) do not provide a delegate, so skip
+  // building the factory to avoid dereferencing a null delegate.
+  if (!ExtensionsAPIClient::Get()->GetWebstorePrivateAPIDelegate())
+    return;
   PendingApprovalsShutdownNotifierFactory::GetInstance();
 }
 
